<h1>Gilles Snowcat</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://gilles-snowcat.com/gilles-snowcat-now.html">gilles-snowcat.com/gilles-snowcat-now.html</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Brussels

Belgium
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Singer, songwriter, experimental artist, life aesthet, muzzy instrumentist, psychotic composer.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I give your ego some pleasure time by singing love songs after dark.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Life's voyage reaches the level of being fantastic when art comes in the picture.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
If life's a stage, I'm the one who keeps the key of the backstage door.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Black Vinyl, White Powder" by Simon Napier-Bell
</p>

